  "text": "Conversely, if there exists a kernel function which corresponds to the inner product between ϕ(x) and ϕ(x ′ ), then the use of the kernel formulation would be beneficial. The existence of such an inner product is guaranteed when the kernel function is positive semidefinite. Such a kernel function is called a Mercer kernel or a reproducing kernel [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . There are many kernel functions whose computational complexity is independent of d ′ . A typical example would be the polynomial kernel (of order c):",
